name: Vrajesh Sharma
shortProjectDescription: ShipIt or SkipIt is an AI-powered GitHub project reviewer designed to simulate how a senior developer evaluates a project. It analyzes repository to provide honest feedback, constructive suggestions, and a final verdict - Ship It, Almost There, or Skip It.  Along with showcasing practical AI evaluation, the project intentionally demonstrates how bias can be introduced into AI systems. For specific known inputs, the system applies a controlled positive bias as an educational example, highlighting how real-world AI decisions can be influenced by design choices.  The project focuses on transparency, learning, and helping builders understand both technical quality and AI system behavior.

name: Jatin Kevlani
shortProjectDescription: InterviewGPT - AI Mock Interview Platform  An intelligent voice-based mock interview system built using Python, LiveKit, and Next.js. The platform simulates real interview scenarios by allowing users to select their role, experience level, and interview type (technical, HR, or behavioral).  It uses real-time speech recognition, AI-powered questioning, and dynamic follow-up logic to conduct realistic interviews, evaluate responses, and provide structured feedback on communication skills, technical understanding, and confidence.  Designed to help users practice interviews in a realistic environment and improve their performance through interactive, AI-driven conversations.

name: Devansh Rajput
shortProjectDescription: (PC- 3. Developer Tools & Utilities) : Synapse is an advanced AI-powered codebase visualization and analysis tool designed for developers. It allows users to visualize GitHub repositories as interactive file trees, chat with an AI assistant that has deep context of the codebase (using OpenRouter/NVIDIA models), and view file contents with rich syntax highlighting. Built with a modern React/Vite frontend and a serverless Cloudflare Workers backend, it features a glassmorphic UI, supports live website previews, and includes agentic tools for reading files, searching the web, and analyzing repository architecture in real-time.
